<body>

    <h1>Preventative Maintenance Request Information</h1>

    <div class="info">
        <p>
            Preventative maintenance <span class="highlight">(PM)</span> is different from an outage. PM is scheduled work to
            maintain or upgrade equipment and may require temporarily shutting off power to ensure safe conditions.
        </p>
        <p>
            An <span class="highlight">outage</span> is an unplanned event caused by equipment failure, storms, or other factors,
            resulting in the interruption of power.
        </p>
    </div>

    <button onclick="showMoreInfo()">Learn More</button>

    <div id="moreInfo" style="display: none;">
        <p><strong>Preventative Maintenance:</strong> Typically scheduled in advance and communicated to customers. Helps reduce the likelihood of future outages.</p>
        <p><strong>Outages:</strong> Can occur suddenly, and our teams respond as quickly as possible to restore power.</p>
    </div>

    <script>
        function showMoreInfo() {
            var moreInfoDiv = document.getElementById("moreInfo");
            if (moreInfoDiv.style.display === "none") {
                moreInfoDiv.style.display = "block";
            } else {
                moreInfoDiv.style.display = "none";
            }
        }
    </script>

</body>
